<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Goldman Sachs Group Inc. is <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28907528.268558/aHR0cHM6Ly9ueXBvc3Qu=
Y29tLzIwMjIvMDgvMzAvZ29sZG1hbi1zYWNocy1saWZ0cy1jb3ZpZC1wcm90b2NvbHMtdXJnZXM=
td29ya2Vycy1iYWNrLXRvLW9mZmljZS8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb340ba37" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>back in the office</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Wall Street giant Goldman Sachs will lift all =
COVID protocols that have kept some workers away as it pushes all employees=
 to return to the office five days a week after Labor Day, The Post has lea=
rned. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The official memo comes just days before the b=
ank expects all employees to return to its offices five days a week, source=
s add.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThis is another way of Goldman Sachs =
saying, =E2=80=98School=E2=80=99s in session and we want you in person=E2=
=80=99 after Labor Day,=E2=80=9D Wells Fargo bank analyst Mike Mayo told Th=
e Post. =E2=80=9CGoldman is the ultimate customer-facing firm and it=E2=80=
=99s tough to face customers remotely.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is that true? The customers don=E2=80=99t work=
 at Goldman=E2=80=99s office. Sometimes they <em>visit</em> Goldman=E2=80=
=99s offices, sure,=C2=A0but that=E2=80=99s usually a schlep for them and t=
hey mostly prefer not to. Generally if you are facing=C2=A0customers, it is=
 (1) =E2=80=9Cremotely,=E2=80=9D by phone or email or Zoom or whatever, or =
(2) by flying to visit the customers at=C2=A0<em>their=C2=A0</em>offices. (=
Or, preferably, on the golf course.) Showing up at <em>your</em> office eve=
ry day is not all that=C2=A0<em>relevant=C2=A0</em>to client-facing-ness. A=
nd Goldman <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2890752=
8.268558/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29sZG1hbnNhY2hzLmNvbS9tZWRpYS1yZWxhdGlvbnMvcHJlc3=
MtcmVsZWFzZXMvY3VycmVudC9wZGZzLzIwMjEtcTQtcmVzdWx0cy5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cBc72399b9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">had record revenue in 2021</a>, so whatever it wa=
s doing=C2=A0<em>before=C2=A0</em>school was in session seems to have worke=
d fine.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still there is obviously some sort of signal b=
eing sent here, perhaps to clients =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99ll be=
 in the office if you call=E2=80=9D? =E2=80=94=C2=A0but certainly to employ=
ees and potential employees. It is some mix of:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">We have a culture of collaboration, co=
llegiality, mentorship, serendipitous conversations at the water cooler, et=
c., and we all need to be together with each other for that to work.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">We=E2=80=99re hardcore and in the offi=
ce all the time to prove it.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I can imagine that message being =E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0appealing? Not to everyone, but you don=E2=80=99t need everyone. Back wh=
en I was an investment banker (disclosure: at Goldman), there was some sens=
e that some banks were more intense and worked longer hours than others. Bu=
t it was all anecdotal; no bank had, like, a formal seven-days-in-the-offic=
e-a-week policy. By the middle of last decade there was a backlash to the i=
ntensity,=C2=A0and many banks (<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/28907528.268558/aHR0cHM6Ly9zbGF0ZS5jb20vYnVzaW5lc3MvMjAxNC8wNy=
9nb2xkbWFuLXNhY2hzLXByb3RlY3RlZC13ZWVrZW5kcy15b3VuZy1iYW5rZXJzLXdhbnQtbW9uZ=
Xktbm90LXRpbWUuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB671f231b" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">including =
Goldman</a>) instituted formal=C2=A0<em>not</em>-seven-days-a-week policies=
, where junior bankers had =E2=80=9Cprotected weekends=E2=80=9D to prevent =
them from working too hard. But it is possible that investment banking has =
become too boring and too standardized, and that some banks will want to di=
fferentiate themselves as =E2=80=9Cwe are intense,=E2=80=9D and being early=
 and uncompromising to a five-days-in-the-office requirement could be a cru=
de way to signal that. And then the intense young bankers will want to work=
 at Goldman and the more laid-back ones won=E2=80=99t. And then the intense=
 ones will get more of the plum private-equity jobs, because they are inten=
se, and then everyone will want to work at Goldman to get those jobs. It ha=
s historically been hard for an investment bank to=C2=A0<em>visibly=C2=A0</=
em>signal that it is more intense than other investment banks. But return-t=
o-office might create some differences.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or it might not and every bank will match this=
 policy within a week, that is also entirely possible.</p>
